An Act relative to 40B condominium units.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 7 of chapter 183A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting the following new paragraph:-
3 "Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, all purchasers of a
4 condominium unit classified as an affordable unit pursuant to chapter 40B of the General Laws,
5 shall be responsible for paying in full any common expenses as stated in the master deed. The
6 Executive Office of Housing and Livable Communities shall develop a program to provide
7 common expense reimbursements to said purchasers of chapter 40B affordable units. No unit
8 owner in a condominium complex shall be imposed with subsidizing the common expenses of
9 any chapter 40B affordable unit."
